      "name": "<think>\nThis is a simple translation request from English to Simplified Chinese (zh-CN). The text \"Acute Sight\" needs to be translated.\n\n\"Acute\" can mean:\n- 急性的 (medical context)\n- 敏锐的 (pertaining to vision/perception)\n- 严重的\n\n\"Sight\" means:\n- 视力 (vision)\n- 视野 (field of view)\n- 景象 (view/scene)\n\nGiven the domain \"item.name\", this appears to be a game or product name. In this context, \"Acute Sight\" most likely refers to enhanced vision or perception ability, often seen in video games as a skill or item.\n\nThe most appropriate translation would be:\n- 敏锐视觉 (acute vision/enhanced sight)\n\nOr more commonly in gaming contexts:\n- 敏锐视觉 or 锐利视觉\n\nI'll go with \"敏锐视觉\" as it's the most natural and commonly used translation for this type of gaming ability.\n</think>\n\n敏锐视觉",
      "type": "feat",
      "img": "icons/svg/mystery-man.svg",
      "system": {
        "description": {
          "value": "<p><think>\nThe user wants me to translate the text \"Faldric has advantage on Wisdom (Perception) checks that rely on sight.\" from English to Simplified Chinese (zh-CN).\n\nThis is a D&D (Dungeons & Dragons) related text describing a game mechanic. Let me translate it:\n\n- \"Faldric\" - This is a proper name, typically kept as is or transliterated. In D&D context, character names are usually kept in English.\n- \"has advantage\" - 有优势\n- \"on Wisdom (Perception) checks\" - 在感知属性检定上\n- \"that rely on sight\" - 基于视觉的\n\nNote: In Chinese D&D communities, the typical translation would be:\n- \"优势\" for \"advantage\"\n- \"感知\" for \"Wisdom (Perception)\"\n- \"检定\" for \"checks\"\n\nLet me put it together:\n\n\"Faldric在基于视觉的感知属性检定上具有优势。\"\n\nOr more naturally:\n\n\"Faldric 在依赖视觉的感知检定上拥有优势。\"\n\nI think the second version sounds more natural in Chinese. Let me refine it:\n\n\"Faldric 在基于视觉的感知检定上具有优势。\"\n\nThis should be the appropriate translation for the D&D context.\n</think>\n\nFaldric 在基于视觉的感知检定上具有优势。</p>",
          "chat": ""
        },
